        "subject": "LU-17288 osd: HAVE_LDISKFSFS_GETHASH_INODE_ARG gone",
        "message": "LU-17288 osd: HAVE_LDISKFSFS_GETHASH_INODE_ARG gone\n\nWith patch \"ldiskfs: Parallel configure tests for ldiskfs\"\naarch64 Ubuntu 20.04 build fails with message\n\nin definition of macro ‘e_ldiskfsfs_dirhash’\nexpected ‘const struct inode *’ but argument is of type ‘const char *’\n\nHAVE_LDISKFSFS_GETHASH_INODE_ARG macros have been removed, but still\nused in osd_iam_lvar.c. This patch changes it to the\nHAVE_LDISKFSFS_DIRHASH_WITH_DIR\n\nFixes: 5579168(\"LU-13485 ldiskfs: Parallel configure tests for ldiskfs\")\nSigned-off-by: Artem Blagodarenko <ablagodarenko@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Ie5791b49a06b0da635c87682b81736b0260be10d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
